Three more reasons why not to do it now:
1. This code was never tested with real hardware, better keep it simple as it may need change when we get to the customer;
2. Given the above #1 we implemented a design in which we dump the configuration passed to Ansible as unchanged as possible to the NetApp Trident application so that we can easily iterate on customer site. This means that ansible list and dictionaries are dumped to json. "username" and "passowrd" is just one option of many more (that we don't even know and understand at the moment);
3. Since NetApp team will release helm charts in April, we will most likely have to redesign this (Brent told us that this is the path forward). Therefore we will remove it from Ansible and move it to a StarlingX standalone application.

